就是那样 你知道的 圣像被祝福了 当然 通过你的信心

32
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:54,688
the deity is blessed. You are praying, you are
worshipping, because in the Hindu tradition
神像被祝福了 你正在祈祷 你正在做礼拜 因为在印度的传统中

33
00:02:55,066 --> 00:02:58,777
we don’t see any difference
between the deity and God.
我们视神像和神是无差别的

34
00:02:59,400 --> 00:03:04,044
We worship the deity the
same as worshipping God
我们崇拜神像和崇拜神是一样的

35
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:09,844
due to that blessing, due to that
infusing of that life force inside it.
因为那祝福 因为那内在生命力的灌注

36
00:03:10,110 --> 00:03:12,977
So, that essence
we are worshipping.
所以 那我们崇拜的本质

37
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,800
We are not
worshipping the stone.
我们不是在崇拜石头

38
00:03:16,822 --> 00:03:20,800
We are worshipping the essence
of God which is present everywhere.
我们崇拜神出现在任何地方的本质

39
00:03:22,660 --> 00:03:26,955
So, during the prayer, there are
many mantras which are chanted.
所以 在祈祷的过程中 有很多颂歌被唱诵

40
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:30,755
While chanting
these mantras
当唱诵这些颂歌时

41
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:36,311
those who have faith,
they are invoking
那些有信心的人他们在呼唤

